# Backend Environment Configuration

## Development
```bash
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
LOG_LEVEL=debug
```

## Required Environment Variables
```bash
# OpenAI API Configuration (for Phase 3)
OPENAI_API_KEY=your_openai_api_key_here

# Server Configuration
NODE_ENV=development
PORT=3000
HOST=localhost

# Logging
LOG_LEVEL=debug

# File Upload
MAX_FILE_SIZE=500MB
UPLOAD_DIR=./temp/uploads

# Cost Tracking (Phase 3)
COST_TRACKING_ENABLED=true
COST_ALERT_THRESHOLD=1.00

# Video Processing
VIDEO_TIMEOUT_MINUTES=60
MAX_VIDEO_DURATION_HOURS=1
```

## Production Configuration
For production deployment on Railway/Heroku:
1. Use environment variables from platform dashboard
2. Set `NODE_ENV=production`
3. Use remote database/storage
4. Enable HTTPS only
5. Set appropriate cost thresholds
